2.3 Corollaries and Remarks

Corollary 2.2 (Regularity of the surface temperature).
Under the same assumptions, $T|_{\Gamma_{\text{win}}} \in \mathcal{C}^{0,\alpha}([0,T])$ for some $\alpha > 0$. Hence the deposition ODE‚Äôs coefficients are H√∂lder continuous, guaranteeing classical differentiability of $\delta_{\text{film}}$.

Remark 2.3 (Comparison with previous formulations).
The ALE approach removes the need to handle the moving boundary as a free boundary with unknown regularity; instead, the mesh velocity is prescribed by the recession model (which itself depends on $\delta_{\text{film}}$ via a smoothing operator). This is physically justified because the recession rate is slow relative to thermal diffusion, so the ALE mapping can be constructed a priori by solving an auxiliary elliptic problem.

