A.1.1 MIEKF‚ÄëPCE Module

The Polynomial Chaos Expansion (PCE) propagates uncertainty through the dynamics. The state dimension $n = 20$ (reduced-order model of temperature field). We use a total degree $p=3$ polynomial chaos with

n_{\text{pce}} = \binom{n+p}{p} = \binom{23}{3} = 1771

basis terms. The cost per cycle is dominated by:

¬∑ Computing the PCE coefficients: $O(n_{\text{pce}} \cdot n^2) \approx 1771 \times 400 = 7.1\times10^5$ FLOPs.
